Initiation season will be suspended, according to the National House of Traditional Leaders. It's made the call to help in the fight against the spread of coronavirus in the country. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Initiation season will be suspended, according to the National House of Traditional Leaders. It's made the call to help in the fight against the spread of coronavirus in the country. “These are desperate times and they call for desperate measures, they call for hard for decision,” said Inkosi Sipho Mahlangu of the National House of Traditional Leaders. READ: Decrease in serious crimes due to unavailability of alcohol: Cele However, the decision is not enjoying consensus yet - especially in the Eastern Cape. The traditional leaders' group says it'll continue to do all it can to save lives. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.